UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030440768090086X
AB  - This paper illustrates the significance of employing data analysis together with standard econometric techniques. A detailed analysis of the same data base used by Tobin (1950), Chetty (1968) and Maddala (1971) indicates (i) the existence of two outliers, and (ii) the presence of serially correlated residuals. It is shown that the conventional estimation and hypothesis testing techniques employed by these authors are extremely sensitive to these two factors.
